- Git Commands


git init (initialize a local git repo)

git add * (add all files to be stage to commit to local repo)

git commit -m "give it a relevant and appropriate message"

git branch (show existing branch)

git branch --list (show all branches you have locally)

git branch -M main (switch from existing branch to main)

git remote add origin https://github.com/Vincent-SWE/day2_sdfworkshop.git (linking your remote repo)

git push -u origin main (origin refers to your remote repo. You are pushing from your remote repo to your main branch)

git pull


git add README.md (to check in only this file)